A basic name service switch module to resolve Android users and groups,
allowing a chroot system on Android to be able to resolve UIDs and GIDs on
Android-created files, as well as assigning local users to Android groups for
permission purposes

Contact:
 Robin McCorkell <rmccorkell@karoshi.org.uk>

Installation:
 Run 'make' to compile and link the program
 Run 'make install' as root to install the program
 Configure /etc/nsswitch.conf to use 'aid' for both passwd and group lookups
